SBI has broken the trend line support & is now heading towards the demand zone, it has already shown a bounce from the zone earlier. Demand zones rarely work as support multiple times so the chances of it breaking down are higher than it bouncing from there. Once it breaks the demand zone it will fall quickly.
HDFC Bank rangebound - wait for break

HDFC Bank is trading in a range since 14 Nov 22. So far it is respecting the demand zone & is bouncing every time it enters it. I would prefer it to break the top side or the bottom side of the range with good volumes before taking any position. If you like to play ranges then you can sell at the top & buy at the bottom of the range.
